  <text>
    <front>
      <div type="printedheader">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_4610_p1"> <seg type="com">
                        <note type="addendum" xml:id="K_4610_c0">Nachträgliche Notiz oben links von Eschers Hand mit Bleistift: <bibl>
                                <supplied type="unclear">8/4</supplied>
                            </bibl>.</note>
                    </seg> <lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <fw>THE PATENT <lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>
			TUNNELING<lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>
			&amp; MINING MACHINE<lb xml:id="p1-l4"/>
			COMPANY<lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>
			LIMITED</fw>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_4610_p2">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>5, Great Winchester <choice>
                        <abbr>St.</abbr>
                        <expan>Street (Strasse)</expan>
                    </choice> Buildings<lb xml:id="p1-l7"/>
                    <fw>
                        <del>8, Old Jewry</del> <placeName type="place" key="London (UK)">London</placeName> <choice>
                            <abbr>E. C.</abbr>
                            <expan>Eastern Central (östlicher Stadtteil)</expan>
                        </choice> </fw>
                </p>
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_4610_p3">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>
          <date when="1872-03-01">
            <choice>
                            <abbr>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> </abbr>
                            <expan>first (erstens)</expan>
                        </choice> March <fw>
					18<del>6</del> </fw>72</date>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="address">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_4610_p4">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l9"/> To the Chairman of the<lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>
          <choice>
                        <abbr>St.</abbr>
                        <expan>Sankt / Sanct / Saint (heilig)</expan>
                    </choice> Gothard
					Railway Company
					<lb xml:id="p1-l11"/>
                    <placeName type="place" key="Bern (Stadt)">Berne</placeName> </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_4610_p5">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l12"/> Sir</p>
      </div>
    </front>
    <body>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_4610_p6">
                <lb xml:id="p1-l13"/> Having been informed that you are<lb xml:id="p1-l14"/> about to commence the <placeName type="place" key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">St.
				Gothard</placeName> Tunnel,<lb xml:id="p1-l15"/> I beg to forward for the information of your<lb xml:id="p1-l16"/> Board a
				printed extract from the report of<lb xml:id="p1-l17"/> The <persName type="person" key="Larcy Charles de">Minister of Public Works</persName> of <placeName type="place" key="Frankreich">France</placeName> <lb xml:id="p1-l18"/>
				relating to our rock-boring machine; and I<lb xml:id="p1-l19"/> beg to intimate that my Company is
				prepared<lb xml:id="p1-l20"/> to enter into negotiations with you for driving<lb xml:id="p1-l21"/> the heading of
				any tunnels required. </p>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_4610_p7">
                <lb xml:id="p1-l22"/> Captain <persName type="person" key="Penrice Herbert Newton">Penrice</persName>, late Royal Engineers, the<lb xml:id="p1-l23"/> Patentee and
				consulting engineer of this Company,<lb xml:id="p1-l24"/> will be at <placeName type="place" key="Bern (Stadt)">Berne</placeName> shortly, and, on my
				hearing<lb xml:id="p1-l25"/> from you regarding this matter, I shall be<lb xml:id="p1-l26"/> happy to ask him to
				call on you to give you<lb xml:id="p1-l27"/> any further information you require. </p>
    </body>
    <back>
      <div type="closer">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_4610_p8">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l28"/> I am, Dear Sir<lb xml:id="p1-l29"/> Yours very truly
				</p>
      </div>
      <div type="address">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_4610_p9">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l30"/>
					 Major <lb xml:id="p1-l31"/> Chairman </p>
      </div>
    </back>
